results.name: Expansion of Product_{k>=1} (1 - k^k*x^k).
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..386
formula: a(0) = 1 and a(n) = -(1/n) * Sum_{k=1..n} A294645(k)*a(n-k) for n > 0. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Nov 09 2017
maple: seq(coeff(series(mul((1-k^k*x^k),k=1..n),x,n+1), x, n), n = 0 .. 20); # _Muniru A Asiru_, Oct 31 2018
mathematica: terms = 18; CoefficientList[Product[(1 - k^k*x^k), {k, 1, terms}] + O[x]^(terms), x] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Nov 11 2017 *)
program: (MAGMA) m:=20; R<x>:=PowerSeriesRing(Rationals(), m); Coefficients(R! ( (&*[(1 - k^k*x^k): k in [1..m]]) )); // _G. C. Greubel_, Oct 31 2018
